The Telegraph - Calcutta
 A months tune-up with Paes enough, says Bhupathi
 Bhupathi feels nothing tops an Olympic gold New Delhi: Mahesh Bhupathi said on Tuesday that he and Leander Paes would pair up on Tour a month before the Athens Olympics to get into the groove for the mega event. According to the junior partner of the three-time Grand Slam champion team, the two will come together at the start of the hardcourt season, around mid-July. The Olympic tennis event gets underway on August 15. The Olympics are different. One month would be enough to get our rhythm going. Well be ready for the Games after playing three-four events, Bhupathi said in an interview via e-mail. The $380,000 Mercedez-Benz Cup in Los Angeles starts on July 12, followed by the $600,000 RCA Championships in Indianapolis and two Masters Series meets in Toronto and Cincinnati. Bhupathis logic is obviously to peak at the right time. At the same time, he and Paes would like to ensure that their ranking remains high enough to earn a high seeding in Athens. Bhupathi is currently No. 5 on the doubles entry list and Paes is 20. For Bhupathi, an Olympic gold would be the most coveted metal to adorn his cupboard that already contains seven Grand Slam trophies. Nothing can come ahead of an Olympic gold. It is something every athlete dreams of winning...  (PTI)  Copyright 
